            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-biography field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p class="x"><span>Michael Martin is an Operating Executive focused on the Financial Services sector. He is based in New York.</span></p>
<p class="x"><span>Prior to joining Carlyle, Mr. Martin was a Managing Director at Warburg Pincus LLC from 2009 to 2024. At Warburg, Mr. Martin was the Head of Financial Services and a member of the Executive Management Group. Previously, Mr. Martin was Vice Chairman and Managing Director of UBS Investment Bank, where he also served as a member of the UBS Investment Bank Board and its Global Executive Committee. He also held senior positions at Credit Suisse First Boston and practiced corporate law at Wachtell, Lipton, Rosen &amp; Katz. Mr. Martin was a law clerk for the Honorable Stephen Reinhardt of the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit. Mr. Martin has served on numerous public and private company boards.</span></p>
<p class="x"><span>Currently, Mr. Martin is an independent director of IntraFi, an Arlington, Virginia based company serving the banking industry. Mr. Martin is also a Trustee of the Inner City Scholarship Fund in New York City.</span></p>
<p class="x"><span>Mr. Martin holds a B.A. in Economics from Claremont McKenna College and a J.D. from Columbia University School of Law.</span></p></div>
      
